Program: The Documentary
Title: Episode One
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ggb4y
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 15 May 2011
In the space of just over ten days in March 2011, the United Nations Security Council passed two of its most significant, emphatic and far-reaching resolutions in decades. Claire Bolderson looks at how the world body used a new-found strength to intervene militarily in Libya and Ivory Coast and assesses how the decisions have changed the course of these two brutal conflicts. Show less